To make pita make a basic Pizza dough (60% hydration).

To make 6 pitas:

Mix @flour{270%g}, @water{160%ml}, @salt{6%g}, @olive oil{12%g} and @yeast.

Mix and let rest over night, if possible. 

Split into 6 dough balls of 75g each. Let them rest for at least ~{1%h}.

Roll out into 1cm thick disks. Let rest again for at least ~{45%min}. THen bake at 250&deg; for 7 minutes. Do not open the oven door while baking.

Let cool on cooling rack.